# PR-B §1.6 — service-role allowlist for the agent runtime.
#
# Files in apps/web-platform/{server,lib} that legitimately import
# `createServiceClient` or `getServiceClient`. The CI grep gate
# (.github/workflows/ci.yml, "service-role-allowlist-gate" job)
# rejects any other importer.
#
# CODEOWNERS pins this file: @jeanderuelle approval is required to add
# a path. Without this, an attacker-modeled PR could add a service-role
# import AND its allowlist line in one commit and the gate would pass.
#
# Format: one path per line, RELATIVE TO REPO ROOT (not apps/web-platform).
# Comments and blank lines are ignored by the gate.
#
# Each path declares one of:
#   - PERMANENT: legitimate by design (auth-domain RPC, signature-
#     verified webhook, bulk sweep with no per-tenant key, etc.)
#   - TRANSITIONAL: enumerated in a follow-up PR's spec; remove the
#     line when that PR migrates the call sites.

# ── Permanent service-role surface ────────────────────────────────────

# Defines `createServiceClient` / `getServiceClient`. The functions
# themselves must reside somewhere; this is the canonical home.
apps/web-platform/lib/supabase/service.ts

# Thin re-export shim (`export { ... } from "./service"`). Historical
# import path; new code should import from `./service` directly.
apps/web-platform/lib/supabase/server.ts

# Tenant-client factory. Uses service-role only for the auth-domain
# `precheck_jwt_mint` RPC (rate-limit + jti generation). Tenant data
# reads/writes go through `createTenantClient(jwt)` (per PR-B §1.1).
apps/web-platform/lib/supabase/tenant.ts

# BYOK lease — reads `api_keys` via tenant-scoped client INSIDE the
# lease body. Service-role here is for the auth-domain RPC plumbing
# (`mintFounderJwt` chain). Lease never bypasses RLS for tenant data.
apps/web-platform/server/byok-lease.ts

# Bulk sweeps in agent-runner.ts at `cleanupOrphanedConversations`
# and `startInactivityTimer`. Both are staleness-keyed
# (`last_active < cutoff`) — no per-tenant key, no userId in scope.
# `getFreshTenantClient(userId)` is structurally inapplicable
# (per type-design F2 + architecture F1). The user-scoped sites in
# the same file MUST migrate (per spec tasks §1.5.1).
apps/web-platform/server/agent-runner.ts

# ── PR-C/PR-D closeouts (#3244 §2 + §4) ──────────────────────────────
#
# 7 files fully migrated to tenant in PR-C and REMOVED from this
# allowlist (no entries below for them): conversations-tools,
# session-sync, conversation-writer, lookup-conversation-for-path,
# current-repo-url, kb-document-resolver, kb-route-helpers.
#
# cc-dispatcher.ts fully migrated to tenant in PR-D §4 (attachments-
# storage moved from service-role to `getFreshTenantClient(userId)`,
# the last remaining service-role-bypassed write path in that file)
# and REMOVED from this allowlist.
#
# 3 files retain a service-role import for a load-bearing
# auth-bootstrap or storage-injection surface that the tenant migration
# cannot cover. Each gets its own PERMANENT rationale below.

# PERMANENT — WS auth handshake (server/ws-handler.ts:1947
# supabase.auth.getUser(token)) validates the operator-supplied token
# BEFORE userId exists. Auth-domain bootstrap, structurally pre-tenant-
# JWT. All 13 tenant data sites in this file migrated in PR-C §2.10.
apps/web-platform/server/ws-handler.ts

# PERMANENT — HTTP Bearer-token validation (server/api-messages.ts:36
# supabase.auth.getUser(token)) for the /api/conversations/:id/messages
# route. Auth-domain bootstrap, pre-tenant-JWT. The 2 tenant data sites
# (:55 conversations SELECT, :79 messages SELECT) migrated in PR-C §2.2.
apps/web-platform/server/api-messages.ts

# PERMANENT — sum_user_mtd_cost RPC is REVOKE EXECUTE FROM authenticated
# (migration 027:68). Per-row `WHERE user_id = uid` + RPC call must stay
# service-role; a tenant-JWT call would 42501 silently. The 1 tenant
# data site (:96 conversations SELECT) migrated in PR-C §2.3.
apps/web-platform/server/api-usage.ts

# ── Account / process-level helpers (unchanged by PR-C / PR-D) ───────
#
# Re-evaluated post-PR-C; migration requires either user-scoped JWT
# (account-delete) or process-scoped infrastructure that has no founder
# identity (concurrency, notifications). Out of PR-C scope.
apps/web-platform/server/account-delete.ts
apps/web-platform/server/concurrency.ts
apps/web-platform/server/notifications.ts

# Shared per-turn cost writer (PR #3626). Service-role required for the
# atomic `increment_conversation_cost` + `write_byok_audit` RPCs which
# are SECURITY DEFINER + service-role-only by migrations 017/037/042.
# Both callers (agent-runner.ts, cc-dispatcher.ts) are already on this
# allowlist for the same posture; the helper inherits.
apps/web-platform/server/cost-writer.ts

# DSAR Art. 15 + Art. 20 self-serve export worker (#3637, plan rev-2).
# Service-role is load-bearing per Q-credential / R-extra1 / C1: an
# in-process worker that authenticates as the data subject would
# require either storing per-user JWT-at-rest (credential-vault risk
# class) or minting per-user session JWTs at runtime (no Supabase
# admin primitive demonstrated for that). C1 alternative: service-role
# + mandatory per-row `WHERE owner_id = $1` (file-parse lint AC30 in
# `dsar-worker-per-row-where.test.ts`) + `assertReadScope` runtime
# invariant on every result set (AC12) + cross-tenant golden fixture
# integration test (AC15). Two-layer defense.
apps/web-platform/server/dsar-export.ts
